India , Sri Lanka Most Suitable for Investment in
KATHMANDU , November 18 ( Xinhua ) -- A World Bank economist said here Wednesday that among member countries of the South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation ( SAARC ) , India and Sri Lanka have the best environments for foreign investment .
" It 's difficult to say at the moment .
I would think it 's either India or Sri Lanka that would come in best , " John Williamson , the World Bank 's chief economist for South Asia , told a press conference .
Williamson was on a three-day visit in Kathmandu which ended Wednesday .
When asked which SAARC country would develop faster in the new millennium , he said " that 's very difficult to say . "
" But if you ask me what would be my most likely bet , I think I probably say India , " he added .
The SAARC , formed in December 1985 to promote economic and social development in the region , groups Bangladesh , Bhutan , India , the Maldives , Nepal , Pakistan and Sri Lanka .
